snippet.textDisplay: I interpreted it as this: the body of Palpatine was his original corpse. It looked dead and decayed, and the contraption he was connected to reminded me of a marionette. It would be pretty cool if his evil spirit survived, and the body was recovered. His spirit was then controlling the puppet body until he was able to steal Rey and Kylos life force, which he used to heal the body and re-enter it, shown when the life returns to the previously “dead” eyes!

snippet.textDisplay: The Last Jedi set up a very plausible explanation for how Palpatine could’ve survived namely that he just did what Luke did. He projected his presence to the Death Star but he wasn’t actually there. I was convinced this was going to be the explanation because it would’ve also fit in with Lucas’ poetic intentions i.e. Luke projecting himself to Crait as a distraction in order to save the resistance, is the opposite of Palpatine luring the rebels into a trap with his presence on the Death Star.
